Rating: 3
De-lish! I let the spice rub "marinate" our salmon steaks for about an hour-and-a-half. I doubled the garlic called for and omitted the butter. This recipe is easy to prepare, especially if your a "fish novice" like me. Like many of you we prepared this on the grill. Good company dish. I served it with an easy mango salsa: 1-2 mangos, diced, 1/3 cup finely diced red onion, 2-3 TBLSP cilantro, 1 TBSLP Ortega diced jalepenos, 1 tsp. fresh lime juice. -- Laura

